  content: "To understand the features customers would immediately start using, the team took a lean approach, talking directly to real customers. Working side-by-side with these customers, the team developed, tested and iterated prototypes. Early on, they began to understand exactly which specific features customers would immediately pay for and use."
  image: "/project-stories/reed-learning/feedback.jpg"
  image_description: "User feedback gathered and shared"

new_product:
  title: "New product in the hands of customers within weeks"
  content: "Within just a few weeks of collaborating together, the team were able to fully prototype and build a working digital Ruby on Rails product that addressed a specific, validated user need, which was then immediately adopted by several active customers. Sharing this result with stakeholders then increased their confidence that this transformation had already began to show results which were not only benefitting the internal team, but also the customer."
  image: "/project-stories/reed-learning/app.jpg"
  image_description: "First application launched"

